<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3904] Similarity javadocs look ugly if created with java7&apos;s javadoc</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3904</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The captions used to illustrate the formulas are tables here:&lt;br/&gt;
in jdk 5/6 the table is centered nicely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But with java7&apos;s javadocs (I think due to some css styles changes?),&lt;br/&gt;
the table is not centered but instead stretched.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we just need to center this table with a different technique?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have a look at &lt;a href=&quot;http://people.apache.org/~rmuir/java7-style-javadocs/org/apache/lucene/search/Similarity.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://people.apache.org/~rmuir/java7-style-javadocs/org/apache/lucene/search/Similarity.html&lt;/a&gt; to see what I mean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: these javadocs are under TFIDFSimilarity.java in trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
